<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-22T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-22T13:00:00-05:00" n="371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/620: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-22T13:00:00-05:00">April 22, 1939—1
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>107. The Department has noted that for the first time in many weeks
                                no telegraphic report has been received from our offices in China of
                                new bombings of American property by Japanese planes. It is
                                suggested that you might care to mention this to the appropriate
                                Japanese authorities when suitable opportunity offers.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>